      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 32 九三</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>九三：不恆其德，或承之羞，貞吝。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The third NINE, undivided, shows one who does not continuously maintain his virtue. There are those who will impute this to him as a disgrace. However firm he may be, there will be ground for regret.</seg>
      </tuv>
